Run a fleet node

Usage: sleet run [OPTIONS] --node-id <NODE_ID> <ROOT>

Arguments:
  <ROOT>
          Fleet root URL, e.g. s3://ops/sleet/

Options:
      --node-id <NODE_ID>
          Node identity; must be unique within the fleet

      --services <SERVICES>
          Services this node offers

          Possible values:
          - gc:                    Garbage collection
          - compactor-coordinator: Standalone compaction coordinator (RFC-0025)
          - compaction-workers:    Compaction workers (RFC-0025)
          - mirror:                Mirroring to per-database targets (RFC 0002)
          
          [default: gc,compactor-coordinator,compaction-workers,mirror]

      --max-mirror-jobs <MAX_MIRROR_JOBS>
          Maximum (database, target) mirror jobs copying or pruning on this node at once. Default: the machine's available parallelism

      --rclone <RCLONE>
          Path to the rclone binary, for mirror targets with copier = "rclone"

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
